gomodel:SYNGO_4905  a    owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment     "Rationale: The study shows the existence of a synaptically localized ATG-9 pool that undergoes exo-endocytosis and localizes at a subset of synaptic vesicles in C. elegans. The exo-endocytosis of ATG-9 is important for synaptic authopagy.\nAuthors also show that ATG9A localizes at presynapses in mammalian synapses (Fig 6a-c, g-i; Fig 7b-c).. Experimental description: They used transgenic animals expressing ATG-9::GFP. The antibody against Atg9A (ab108338) is KO-validated." ;
        lego:modelstate  "production" ;
        dc:contributor   "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date          "2023-01-28" ;
        dc:title         "SYNGO_CC_4905" ;
        pav:providedBy   "https://syngo.vu.nl" .

